  <summary date="2021-09-20T14:37:25Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Real Corporate Profits Tax Act of 2021

This bill imposes an additional 7% tax on the adjusted net book income of a corporation that exceeds $100 million. It also allows a credit for a taxpayer, other than an S corporation, for a specified percentage of the taxpayer's net regular tax liability.</summary>
